ğŸ” What I Learned:
A Binary Search Tree is a type of binary tree where:

Every node has at most two children â€“ left and right.

The left child contains values less than the parent, and

The right child contains values greater than the parent.

This structure allows for efficient search, insert, and delete operations â€” all in O(log n) time (in a balanced BST).

ğŸ› ï¸ What I Built:
I wrote a simple BinarySearchTree class with an initial check to see if the tree is empty.

ğŸ’» Code Snapshot:
js
Copy
Edit
class Node {
    constructor(value) {
        this.value = value;
        this.left = null;
        this.right = null;
    }
}

class BinarySearchTree {
    constructor() {
        this.root = null;
    }

    isEmpty() {
        return this.root === null;
    }
}

const bst = new BinarySearchTree();
console.log("Tree is empty:", bst.isEmpty()); // true
